@matthiasblaesing 

> I don't think the `#1` in the commit message is a deal breaker. That github decided to try to gather information from plain text insteaf of structured information is a problem of github, not Brad. Try to add some random "@" into messages and a random number of people get CCed.

I didn't mean that. Actually, I approved this. I just would like to avoid unnecessary notification/link. I meant I suggest use another one (from next time; It's OK with me to merge this as it is) if we need not use `#xx` absolutely. It's a problem of GitHub, but it's better if we can avoid that, I think.

